Key Match Events: Rassie van der Dussen scored 133 runs.
South Africa posted a total of 357-4.
David Miller scored 53 runs off 30 balls.
Tim Southee dismissed Rassie van der Dussen.
Post-Match Reflections: South Africa captain Temba Bavuma praised the team's clinical display.
Rassie van der Dussen expressed satisfaction with the team's performance.
New Zealand stand-in captain Tom Latham acknowledged the pressure from South Africa's massive partnership.
Miscellaneous Highlights: South Africa dislodged India from the top of the points table based on net run rate.
New Zealand lost the bowling services of seamer Matt Henry due to a right hamstring problem.
James Neesham was struck on the hand but did not suffer broken bones.
